OL,5, Train drivers have been offered a 4%   
OL,6, pay rise for two years in a row by the 
OL,7, body which represents rail companies in
OL,8, a bid to end strike action.            
OL,10,FThe Rail Delivery Group (RDG) has made 
OL,11,Fits first offer to Aslef, the union for
OL,12,Ftrain drivers, after several strikes.  
OL,14,FThe deal includes a backdated pay rise 
OL,15,Fof 4% for 2022 and a 4% increase this  
OL,16,Fyear, but it also hinges on changes to 
OL,17,Fworking practices.                     
OL,19,FAslef told the BBC its officials had   
OL,20,Fnot seen the offer yet.                
